 <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby Loses to Newton\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=145\n| date = 1921-06-20\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210620.2.90\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = Jones, L Newdick\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = A Rae, [[Dougie McGregor]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = T Hill\n}}\n\n===Round 9===\nRound 9 saw the opening of Carlaw Park and the first ever match played on its soil. City defeated Maritime by 10 points to 8 in front of 7000 spectators. The other two matches for this round were postponed. The captains of both [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] and [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] decided to postpone the match, though the majority of the [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] players were unaware of this arrangement and arrived at the ground ready to play. While on the same day the Fire Brigade players were called to a warehouse fire in the city at mid-day and were tired and late arriving to the ground so the match was abandoned.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =First Game on Carlaw Park/City Defeats Maritime/An Exciting Contest\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17818\n| date = 1921-06-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210627.2.128.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 10\u20138\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\">{{cite news\n| title =First Game on Carlaw Park/City Defeats Maritime/An Exciting Contest\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17818\n| date = 1921-06-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210627.2.128.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Maritime\n| try1 = H Hawkes, Harry Francis\n| con1 = W Minogue\n| pen1 = W Minogue (1 mark)\n| try2 = Lunn, [[Ivan Littlewood]]\n| con2 = [[Eric Grey]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = PPD\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\" />\n| away = Newton\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = PPD\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\" />\n| away = Fire Brigade\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 2\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Round 10===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = 34\u20133\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Good Play On Carlaw Park/Marist Overwhelms Newton\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=157\n| date = 1921-07-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210704.2.93\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Ernie Herring]] 2, [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]], [[Arthur Singe]], Puha, A Eustace, P Gallagher\n| con1 = [[Ernie Herring]], [[Bill Stormont]], [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]], Carroll 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 3700\n| referee = T Hill\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 18\u201311\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Good Play On Carlaw Park/Ponsonby 18, Shore 11\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=157\n| date = 1921-07-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210704.2.93\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Devonport\n| try1 = [[Dougie McGregor]], Ben McGregor, [[Sam Lowrie]], W McNeil\n| con1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Dougie McGregor]]\n| try2 = J Price, Cargill, [[Alf Townsend]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| drop2 = McAneny\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| att