 = S Delaney\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = H Clayton\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 21\u20135\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby 21, Fire Brigade 5\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17830\n| date = 1921-07-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210711.2.101.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Fire Brigade\n| try1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 2, E McGregor, W Edwards, Bill Walsh\n| con1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = R Coates\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = L Hemming\n}}\n\n==Roope Rooster Knockout Competition==\nThe first round match between [[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]] and Maritime ended controversially with [[Marist Saints|Marist]] complaining that the match had finished early (when they were trailing by 10 points to 8. They protested and the match was replayed with Maritime winning 21 to 10.\n\nThe final was won by [[City Rovers]] who defeated Maritime in the final in front of a large crowd by 30 points to 14. Over \u00a3230 were taken at the gate which was a record for [[Carlaw Park]], albeit in its first season of use. From this 50 percent went to the Auckland League Sick and Injured Players\u2019 Fund, 25 percent to the Hospital Radium Fund, and 25 percent to the [[St John New Zealand|St. John Ambulance Association]]\n.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =City\u2019s Great Victory/Maritime Defeated/Fine Exhibition at Carlaw Park/Witnessed by 8,000 Spectators\n| page =8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=235\n| date = 1921-10-03\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19211003.2.105\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n\n===Round 1===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 16 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 13\u20137\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =The Roope Rooster/City Defeats Newton\n| pag