5}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Hodges, J Shanahan 2\n| con1 = Nicholls 2\n| pen1 = Nicholls 2 (and 1 mark), Balks\n| try2 = [[Ivan Littlewood]], T Peckham, W McNeil, [[Bill Stormont]], H Hawkes\n| con2 = W Flynn 3, [[Bill Stormont]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Basin Reserve, Wellington\n| attendance =\n| referee = C Snow\n}}\n\n===West Coast v Auckland===\nNo full team lists were published for this match and none of the scorers were listed either in match reports from any newspaper in New Zealand. The match report did however mention that the following players for Auckland performed well: [[Maurice Wetherill]], W Flynn, G Yardley, T Peckham, V Thomas, and [[Bill Stormont]]. It is most likely that Auckland fielded the same touring team that played in Wellington 4 days prior and in Christchurch 3 days later.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = West Coast\n| score = 7\u201347\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V West Coast/An Easy Victory\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17869\n| date = 1921-09-25\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210825.2.105.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Auckland\n| try1 = Unknown x 11\n| con1 = Unknown x 7\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Unknown x 1\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 = Unknown x 1\n| stadium = Greymouth\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Canterbury v Auckland===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 27 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Canterbury\n| score = 14\u201339\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Auckland V Canterbury/Win For Northerners/Thirty-Nine To Fourteen\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17872\n| date = 1921-08-29\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210829.2.93.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Auckland\n| try1 = W Green, [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]], R Watts, W Healey\n| con1 = [[Jim Sanders (rugby league)|Jim Sanders]]\n| pen1 =\n| 