ews\n| title =Marist Old Boys 17, Devonport 9\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17794\n| date = 1921-05-30\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210530.2.130.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Devonport\n| try1 = A Eustace 3, J Hing, P Gallagher\n| con1 = Carroll\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = A Nelson, Morgan, C Nicholson\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 3\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = T Hill\n}}\n\n===Round 6===\nRound 6 was somewhat farcical. Devonport fielded several juniors and when the score got to 14-0 in favour of Maritime very quickly four Maritime players changed teams to make it a more even contest. The remainder of the game more resembled a practice match. While Newton defaulted their match with Fire Brigade as only 6 players turned out. The New Zealand Herald match report stated that \u201ccounter-attractions proving too strong for the Newton players\u201d.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 24-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Defeats Ponsonby\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17800\n| date = 1921-06-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210606.2.105.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-24}}</ref>| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]] 2, [[Alf Townsend]] 2, T Peckham, E Mackie\n| con1 = E Mackie, Unknown x 1\n| pen1 = [[Maurice Wetherill]] 1 mark\n| try2 = Dagnall\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Len Farrant\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 4 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = 5-25\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Maritime 25, Devonport 5\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17800\n| date = 1921-06-06\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210606.2.105.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-24}}</ref>| away = Maritime\n| try1 = Un