d Maritime by 10 points to 8 in front of 7000 spectators. The other two matches for this round were postponed. The captains of both [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] and [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] decided to postpone the match, though the majority of the [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] players were unaware of this arrangement and arrived at the ground ready to play. While on the same day the Fire Brigade players were called to a warehouse fire in the city at mid-day and were tired and late arriving to the ground so the match was abandoned.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =First Game on Carlaw Park/City Defeats Maritime/An Exciting Contest\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17818\n| date = 1921-06-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210627.2.128.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 10-8\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\">{{cite news\n| title =First Game on Carlaw Park/City Defeats Maritime/An Exciting Contest\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17818\n| date = 1921-06-27\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210627.2.128.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Maritime\n| try1 = H Hawkes, Harry Francis\n| con1 = W Minogue\n| pen1 = W Minogue (1 mark)\n| try2 = Lunn, [[Ivan Littlewood]]\n| con2 = [[Eric Grey]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Devonport\n| score = PPD\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\" />\n| away = Newton\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 25 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = PPD\n| report = <ref name=\"autoRefB\" />\n| away = Fire Brigade\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 2\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Round 10===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = 34-3\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Good Play On Carlaw Park/Marist Overwhelms Newton\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=157\n| date = 1921-07-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210704.2.93\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Ernie Herring]] 2, [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]], [[Arthur Singe]], Puha, A Eustace, P Gallagher\n| con1 = [[Ernie Herring]], [[Bill Stormont]], [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league)|John Lang]], Carroll 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 3700\n| referee = T Hill\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 18-11\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Good Play On Carlaw Park/Ponsonby 18, Shore 11\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=157\n| date = 1921-07-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210704.2.93\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Devonport\n| try1 = [[Dougie McGregor]], Ben McGregor, [[Sam Lowrie]], W McNeil\n| con1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Dougie McGregor]]\n| try2 = J Price, Cargill, [[Alf Townsend]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| drop2 = McAneny\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = L Hemming\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 2 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Maritime\n| score = 24-6\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Maritime Beats Fire Brigade\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=157\n| date = 1921-07-04\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210704.2.93\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Fire Brigade\n| try1 = O\u2019Donnell, [[Ivan Littlewood]] 3, Ballyntyne, McGregor\n| con1 = O\u2019Donnell, [[Ivan Littlewood]], G Yardley\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = J Williams, Phil Castles\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Mincham\n}}\n\n===Round 11===\nThe City v Newton game was discontinued at halftime due to the score line. Newton had started the match a man short and the score line had already blown out to 37-5 by the interval.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Marist\n| score = 18-4\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Marist Defeat Maritime\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17830\n| date = 1921-07-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210711.2.101.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Maritime\n| try1 = A Eustace, [[Arthur Singe]], [[John Lang (New Zealand rugby league|John Lang]], Casey\n| con1 = Carroll, Billy Ghent\n| pen1 = [[Arthur Singe]]\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = G Yardley, W Flynn\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = Len Farrant\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 37-5\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Easily Defeat Newton\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17830\n| date = 1921-07-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210711.2.101.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Newton\n| try1 = Unknown 37 points\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = S Delaney\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = S Delaney\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 2\n| attendance = 6000\n| referee = H Clayton\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 21-5\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby 21, Fire Brigade 5\n| page =7\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=LVIII| issue=17830\n| date = 1921-07-11\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19210711.2.101.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| away = Fire Brigade\n| try1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 2, E McGregor, W Edwards, Bill Walsh\n| con1 = [[Dougie McGregor]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = R Coates\n| con2 = Unknown x 1\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = L Hemming\n}}\n\n==Roope Rooster Knockout Competition==\nThe first round match between [[Marist Saints|Marist Old Boys]] and Maritime ended controversially with [[Marist Saints|Marist]] complaining that the match had finished early (when they were trailing by 10 points to 8. They protested and the match was replayed with Maritime winning 21 to 10.\n\nThe final was won by [[City Rovers]] who defeated Maritime in the final in front of a large crowd by 30 points to 14. Over \u00a3230 were taken at the gate which was a record for [[Carlaw Park]], albeit in its first season of use. From this 50 percent went to the Auckland League Sick and Injured Players\u2019 Fund, 25 percent to the Hospital Radium Fund, and 25 percent to the [[St John New Zealand|St. John Ambulance Association]]\n.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =City\u2019s Great Victory/Maritime Defeated/Fine Exhibition at Carlaw Park/Witnessed by 8,000 Spectators\n| page =8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=235\n| date = 1921-10-03\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19211003.2.105\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>\n\n===Round 1===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 16 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 13-7\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =The Roope Rooster/City Defeats Newton\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=LII| issue=169\n| date = 1921-07-18\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19210718.2.91\n| accessdate = 2019-08-25}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]], H Hawkes, [[Ben Davidson (rugby league)|Ben Davidson]]\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| try2 = J Biggs\n| con2 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| pen2 =\n| drop2 = [[Craddock Dufty]]\n| stadium = Carlaw Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = A Ball\n}}\n \n{{ru